Paper: hep-th/9411127

Date: 1994-11-17

Title: Linear connections on matrix geometries

Authors: J. Madore, T. Masson, J. Mourad

Comments: 14p, LPTHE-ORSAY 94/96

Journal-ref: Class. Quant. Grav. 12 (1995) 1429

A general definition of a linear connection in noncommutative geometry hasbeen recently proposed. Two examples are given of linear connections innoncommutative geometries which are based on matrix algebras. They both possessa unique metric connection.